574. clientes (= cluentes those who listen—and do not speak) were manumitted slaves, protected aliens, descendants of these two classes, and others, who attached themselves to some rich man as · patronum cf. the mediaeval baron’s retainers. To have a large number of clientes conferred social distinction.
